      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHARLIE DUTTON (5) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors four starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (17.02) at this track over 300m. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Likely to feature again. LIGHTNING LILY (1) broke a string of placings finishing in the money three on end before a last start seventh (19.90) at Muswellbrook. The form out of last race has been strong. Better than last start and can bounce back. SYMI SURTEE (2) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 0.8 lengths second (17.05) in a Grade 5 at this track. Well placed here and should do much better. FLORELLA (3) defied the market to win last start and can go on with it.",
